---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import FAQ from '../components/FAQ.astro';
import FramedPhoto from '../components/FramedPhoto.astro';
import { serviceSchema } from '../lib/schema';
import { CTA } from '../consts';

// SERVICES — AI visibility + strategy ONLY (no fractional marketing).
// Voice: Full LinkedIn Laura.
const faqs = [
  { question: 'What is an AI visibility audit?', answer: 'It maps where your brand shows up — and gets cited — across AI engines like ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, and Google AI Overviews, and diagnoses why. Not a single "score," but what AI actually says about you and where the gaps are.' },
  { question: 'How is this different from SEO?', answer: 'SEO gets you ranked in a list of links. AI visibility gets you quoted in the answer. They overlap and have to run in the same strategy — you can rank #1 on Google and still be invisible (or uncited) in AI answers.' },
  { question: 'Is it too early to invest in this?', answer: 'No. Brands cited in AI Overviews already earn 35% more organic clicks and 91% more paid clicks than uncited brands on the same query (Seer Interactive, Sept 2025). And AI citations can shift far faster than SEO rankings — the ones you own today can be gone in six weeks.' },
  { question: 'Do you do the implementation?', answer: 'Engagements range from a one-time audit to embedded strategy and content activation. I work directly with brands and as an embedded strategy partner inside agency teams. We scope what you need on a call.' },
  { question: 'Who do you work with?', answer: 'Brands and agencies — including regulated industries like healthcare and MedTech, where I spent years and know the approval chain cold.' },
];
---
<PageLayout
  title="Services"
  description="AI visibility audits and strategy: get your brand cited by AI engines, not just ranked on Google."
  schemas={[serviceSchema()]}
>
  <p class="subhead">ai visibility &amp; strategy</p>
  <FramedPhoto class="img-right" src="/images/laura-laptop-site.jpg" alt="Laura reviewing a website" shape="feather" ratio="4 / 3" reveal />
  <p class="prose">
    The goal is simple: when someone asks AI a question in your category, your
    brand is the answer it gives — and the source it actually cites. Here's the
    catch most people miss: being the answer and being the cited source are two
    different things. I work on both.
  </p>

  <h2>AI Visibility Audit</h2>
  <p class="prose">
    Where you show up — and don't — across ChatGPT, Claude, Perplexity, and Google
    AI, plus the real reason why. I run a manual prompt audit, check your site for
    AI extractability, and map where your brand exists outside your own website
    (because AI builds your identity from the ENTIRE internet, not your homepage).
  </p>

  <h2>AI Visibility Strategy</h2>
  <p class="prose">
    The plan to get cited — built on what your audience actually asks, not a list
    of prompts crowdsourced in a Teams thread. SEO + AEO + GEO in one strategy, not
    three separate workstreams. We fix the existing content before chasing shiny
    new pages.
  </p>

  <h2>Audience Intelligence</h2>
  <p class="prose">
    The real language buyers use, mined from where they talk when no one's watching.
    The most important thing about your audience won't show up in a keyword tool —
    and it's both your creative brief and your AI visibility strategy.
  </p>

  <h2>Content Activation</h2>
  <p class="prose">
    Content engineered to be extracted and quoted by AI — structured so the dice
    are loaded in your favor. In regulated industries, that includes mapping the
    approval chain so the work actually ships instead of dying in legal review.
  </p>

  <h2>The AI Intelligence Loop</h2>
  <p class="prose">
    It all runs as a loop: audience intelligence and brand-identity analysis as
    parallel inputs → a strategy built for AI visibility → content activation →
    monitoring that feeds right back into the intelligence. It compounds. That's
    the point.
  </p>

  <FAQ items={faqs} />

  <p style="margin-top: var(--space-4)">
    <a class="button" href={CTA.calendly}>Let's talk AI visibility</a>
  </p>
</PageLayout>
